<topic id="upload-files-with-oxygen">
  <title><?oxy_comment_start author="Steven" timestamp="20190308T112212+0200" comment="Moved to not_used folder because the web applet method is no longer used (EXM-43091)"?>Copy
    Resources Using <ph keyref="product"/><?oxy_comment_end?></title>
  <body>
    <p>You can use <ph keyref="product"/> to copy your resources to the SharePoint server:<ol
        id="ol_d5z_r5g_nm">
        <li>Configure a new connection to your SharePoint site in the <xref
            href="relational-database-explorer.dita#relational-database-explorer"><uicontrol>Data
              Source Explorer</uicontrol> view</xref>.</li>
        <li>Browse your new SharePoint connection site and select the
              <b><filepath>SitePages</filepath></b> folder.</li>
        <li>Create a folder named <filepath>author-component</filepath> using the <uicontrol>New
            Folder</uicontrol> contextual menu action.</li>
        <li>Upload your resources to this folder using the <uicontrol>Import Files</uicontrol>
          contextual menu action.<p>
            <fig>
              <title>Data Source Explorer View</title>
              <image placement="break" href="../img/browse-sharepoint.png" id="image_urm_lxg_nm"/>
            </fig>
          </p></li>
      </ol></p>
  </body>
